0.body: Welcome to the Derailed Documentation! This documentation is supposed to serve as a way for any wanting developers to use to either reference standards or to make an API library around.
0.title: Welcome

1.body: Basic rundown of some standardized things throughout Derailed and our documentation.
1.title: API Reference

10.body: Creates a Guild, and returns its object . field type name string
10.title: POST : /guilds

11.body: Modifies a Guild, and returns the new object field type name string
11.title: PATCH : /guilds/:guild_id

12.body: Gets a Guild, and returns its object . Requires you to be a member of that Guild.

13.body: Gets the Guild, and returns its its preview .
13.title: GET : /guilds/:guild_id/preview

14.body: Roles are cosmetic or permission-based additions to members which allow them to present themselves differently and allow them to do actions in different forms.
14.title: Roles

15.body: field type id snowflake guild_id snowflake name string permissions permissions position integer
15.title: Role Structure

16.body: Channels are isolated, stateful, and permanently stored objects which can support being sent messages to. Their main purpose is to allow a higher level of abilities else than a single global channel or single Guild channel like in IRC-based chat applications.
16.title: Channel

17.body: While they aren't in the database, nor to Derailed itself, this structure separates channels by type to make a easier reading experience.
17.title: Channel Structure

18.body: Fields put on every channel, no matter the type. field type id snowflake type snowflake
18.title: Common Channel

19.body: Fields put on every channel inside a Guild, no matter the type. field type guild_id snowflake parent_id! snowflake position integer
19.title: Common Guild Channel

20.body: type structure 0 Category Channel 1 Text Channel
20.title: Channel Types

21.body: Users are Derailed's root controllers, they have access to most, or if not all, of our featureset and get supreme reign over bots
21.title: User

22.body: field type id snowflake username string discriminator string email? string flags integer system boolean suspended boolean
22.title: User Structure

23.body: Creates and Registers a new user. Adds an extra token field with your token. field type username string email string password string
23.title: POST : /register

24.body: Creates and Registers a new user. field type username string email string password string discriminator integer-string
24.title: PATCH : /users/@me

25.body: Logs in and makes a new token for an existing account. Adds an extra token field with your token. field type email string password string
25.title: POST : /login

26.body: The Gateway is Derailed's form of implementing real-time communication via websockets.
26.title: Gateway

27.body:
Once you've made a connection to the Gateway, it should send: { "op": 2, "d": { "heartbeat_interval": 45000 }, "s": 0
} While currently heartbeat_interval is static, we suggest using it so in the future your lib will be safe. heartbeat_interval is based in milliseconds.
27.title: Hello (Server)

28.title: Heartbeating (Client/Server)

29.body:
Identifying is not too hard, and only requires one field. Just simply: { "op": 1, "d": { "token": "token" }
}
29.title: Identify (Client)

3.body: ! - This field is nullable ? - This field can be undefined !? - This field can be nullable or undefined
3.title: Field Identifiers

30.body:
In response to an Identify request, the server will give you an info showing you're ready to progress: { "op": 4, "d": { "session_id": "abcdef", "user": {...}, "settings": {...}, "unavailable_guilds": [] }
} session_id is the id given to your session internally. user is, as the name says, your user object. unavailable_guilds a list of guild ids which you were previously in. settings a user settings object.
30.title: Ready (Server)

31.body:
Sent when an event happens. Structured like: { "op": 0, "t": "EVENT_NAME", "d": {...}, "s": 0
} with d being the event data and s being your new sequence.
31.title: Event (Server)

4.body: The entire Derailed API uses Twitter's Snowflake ID, which consists of multiple fields. The fields themselves will be detailed here soon but for now we'll be detailing only the Derailed Epoch. The Epoch for Derailed is the first second of the first of January 2023 or 1672531200000.
4.title: Identification Standard

5.body: In Derailed, depending on the circumstance, integers are unreliable. If an integer goes over 32 bits, we will transform it into a string.
5.title: Integer Reliability

6.body: Permissions may be referred to in two fashions, "bit int" and "permissions" When "bit int" is put, it means an integer holding the permissions itself. When we use "permissions" though, we mean a permissions object: field type allow bit int deny bit int
6.title: Permissions

7.body: Guilds are Derailed's form of letting communities interact with eachother.
7.title: Guild

8.body: field type id snowflake name string flags integer owner_id snowflake permissions bit int a preview guild may also hold available and approximate_presence_count, and a gateway guild will hold an available field.
8.title: Guild Structure

9.body: field type user_id snowflake guild_id snowflake nick! string
9.title: Member Structure
